{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01G8C2dkPvbhHaYpuQ3jx316","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now let me create a comprehensive summary of my findings:\n\n## Research Summary: Title Extraction Key Functions and Patterns\n\nI've successfully located and analyzed all the key files and functions mentioned in your improvement plan. Here's the complete reference:\n\n### **File 1: `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts` (1517 lines)**\n\n#### Core Functions:\n\n| Function | Lines | Summary |\n|----------|-------|---------|\n| **`buildCandidates`** | 537-685 | Generates candidate titles from lines. Handles hyphen-broken lines, ALL_CAPS coalescing, continuation merging, and generates single/2-line/3-line join candidates with dedup via `seen` Set. |\n| **`normalizeOcrTitle`** | 818-872 | Post-processes extracted titles with 3 steps: (1) dictionary-guided repair via `repairOcrText()`, (2) strip section markers with regex, (3) blind digit→letter substitution for ALL_CAPS text only, (4) title-case conversion only if substitution occurred. |\n| **`repairOcrText`** | 798-810 | Applies word-level dictionary-guided OCR repair by splitting text, isolating alphanumeric cores, and calling `repairOcrWord()` on each. |\n| **`repairOcrWord`** | 744-772 | Attempts dictionary lookup of OCR-corrupted words by generating substitution candidates using `OCR_SUBSTITUTIONS` map and checking against `FOOD_DICTIONARY`. Preserves original casing. |\n| **`findBurstEnd`** | 430-506 | Identifies preamble end by: (1) skipping \"PREVIOUS RECIPE OVERFLOW\" blocks, (2) skipping garbled short lines, (3) skipping 5+ consecutive cooking instructions, (4) skipping 3+ consecutive prose lines (lowercase start/continuation). Returns first valid candidate position. **Key threshold: 5 consecutive instructions (line 484).** |\n| **`passesCorroboration`** | 243-268 | Validates candidates via vocabulary corroboration: short candidates (≤3 content words) require 100% match in other lines; longer candidates require ≥67%. Used to filter orphaned multi-title artifacts. |\n| **`isSectionLabel`** | 190-197 | Detects section labels via `SECTION_LABELS` set (case/diacritic-insensitive). Handles OCR variant where leading \"l\" corrupts \"I\" (e.g., \"lngredients\"). |\n| **`looksLikeMetadata`** | 226-228 | Tests text against `METADATA_PATTERNS` regex set (serves/makes/yields, times, yields). |\n\n#### Constants & Patterns:\n\n| Item | Lines | Content |\n|------|-------|---------|\n| **`OCR_ARTIFACT_PATTERN`** | 738 | `/[0-9¡Íí€]/` — matches any digit or OCR corruption characters that might indicate OCR issues. |\n| **`OCR_SUBSTITUTIONS`** | 728-736 | Dictionary mapping OCR artifacts to possible letters: `\"0\": [\"o\"], \"1\": [\"i\", \"l\"], \"4\": [\"a\"], \"5\": [\"s\"], \"¡\": [\"i\"], \"í\": [\"i\", \"l\"], \"€\": [\"e\"]` |\n| **`SECTION_LABELS`** | 115-167 | 70+ labels including English (ingredients, directions, serving, etc.) and Polish equivalents (składniki, przygotowanie, etc.). Includes both process labels and food categories. |\n| **`CATEGORY_SECTION_LABELS`** | 173-183 | Subset of `SECTION_LABELS` for food-group/chapter labels only (e.g., \"vegetables\", \"soups\", \"warzywa\", \"zupy\"). Can legitimately end compound titles. |\n| **`maxPositionalBoost`** | 1048 | **Hard cap of 0.15** on combined positional bonuses (candidate-relative position + first-after-preamble). Prevents over-boosting when both bonuses fire together. |\n\n#### Dedup Filter (Substring Check):\n\n**Location:** Lines 1376-1386 (main dedup logic)\n\n```\nselected = selected.filter((a) => {\n  const aLower = a.text.toLowerCase();\n  // Protect compound titles — these use explicit separators\n  if (/ [+:&] /.test(a.text)) return true;\n  return !selected.some(\n    (b) =>\n      b !== a &&\n      aLower.includes(b.text.toLowerCase()) &&\n      b.text.length < a.text.length\n  );\n});\n```\n\n**Logic:** If candidate `a` is a substring of another candidate `b` and `b` is shorter, remove `a`. Exception: protect compound titles with separators (` + `, ` : `, ` & `). **Shorter always wins** (e.g., \"Pierogi Ruskie\" beats \"Pierogi Ruskie 200g mąki\").\n\nPre-filters (lines 1314-1368) also handle:\n- Sub-section headers followed by ingredients (ALL_CAPS lines)\n- Prefix singles whose continuation join survived\n- Position-0 compound titles protection from distant headers\n\n#### Multi-Title Guard:\n\n**Location:** Lines 1388-1470 (major control flow)\n\n**Three cases:**\n\n1. **≥2 ALL_CAPS survivors** (lines 1397-1426): Keep all, or filter via vocabulary corroboration. Detect if they're section headers (immediately followed by ingredients) vs. actual multi-title page.\n2. **Exactly 1 ALL_CAPS survivor** (lines 1427-1447): If in last 25% of document → likely category footer. Prefer earlier candidates if available.\n3. **Zero ALL_CAPS survivors** (lines 1449-1469): If spread >10 lines apart → body-text leakage, collapse to highest-scoring. If ≤10 lines → likely genuine multi-recipe content, keep all.\n\n#### First-After-Preamble Bonus Logic:\n\n**Location:** Lines 1023-1055\n\n- **Applied to first candidate only** (line 1024)\n- **Bonus amount:** `const preambleBonus = 0.10;` (line 1027)\n- **Capping logic** (lines 1046-1055): Total positional boost (relative position + preamble) capped at `maxPositionalBoost = 0.15`\n\n---\n\n### **File 2: `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/food-dictionary.ts` (146 lines)**\n\n| Item | Lines | Summary |\n|------|-------|---------|\n| **`FOOD_DICTIONARY`** | 7-146 | `Set<string>` of 400+ words: English/Polish ingredients, cooking verbs, dish types, descriptors, and structural recipe title words. Used by `repairOcrWord()` for dictionary-guided OCR repair. All lowercase, diacritic-free for OCR resilience. |\n| **`CATEGORY_SECTION_LABELS`** | — | Referenced in title-extractor, not defined here. (Defined in title-extractor.ts lines 173-183) |\n\n---\n\n## Key Insights\n\n1. **Blind digit→letter substitution** (lines 832-863 of normalizeOcrTitle): Only applied to ALL_CAPS text. Mixed-case text uses per-word logic (digits between lowercase letters → lowercase letters). This prevents over-correction of mixed-case titles.\n\n2. **Dedup substring filter** preserves **shorter candidates** — the opposite of greedy suffix removal. Works correctly because pre-filters remove structural headers that would otherwise block longer forms.\n\n3. **Cooking instruction prologue threshold**: 5+ consecutive cooking instructions (line 484 of findBurstEnd) signal a preamble to skip.\n\n4. **Multi-title guard** is a sophisticated state machine balancing three detection modes (ALL_CAPS density, spread distance, ingredient proximity) to avoid false multi-title collapses.\n\n5. **Corroboration filter** (lines 1402-1404) is applied only when ≥2 ALL_CAPS candidates exist, catching orphaned artifacts from preceding pages.\n\nAll file paths are absolute and ready for reference in your improvement plan implementation."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aae8b6e3734fca12d (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 110306\ntool_uses: 22\nduration_ms: 89340</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b58b8c45-4f2d-433d-859c-e1c4435e3073","uuid":"990735fa-1365-4fab-b51f-98f8d861357a","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Quick exploration: Find the key files and functions mentioned in a title-extraction improvement plan. I need to understand the current structure of:\n\n1. `lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts` - find these specific functions/areas:\n   - `buildCandidates` function\n   - `normalizeOcrTitle` function (specifically the blind digit→letter substitution logic)\n   - `repairOcrText` / `repairOcrWord`\n   - The dedup filter (where `selected = selected.filter(...)` with substring check)\n   - `findBurstEnd` function (specifically the cooking-instruction prologue threshold)\n   - `passesCorroboration` function\n   - The first-after-preamble bonus logic\n   - `isSectionLabel` and `looksLikeMetadata` functions\n   - `OCR_ARTIFACT_PATTERN`\n   - `maxPositionalBoost` cap\n   - The multi-title guard\n\n2. `lib/text-classifier/food-dictionary.ts` - find `FOOD_DICTIONARY` and `CATEGORY_SECTION_LABELS`\n\nFor each, give me the file path, line numbers, and a brief summary of the current code. This is research only - do not modify any files.","agentId":"aae8b6e3734fca12d","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now let me create a comprehensive summary of my findings:\n\n## Research Summary: Title Extraction Key Functions and Patterns\n\nI've successfully located and analyzed all the key files and functions mentioned in your improvement plan. Here's the complete reference:\n\n### **File 1: `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts` (1517 lines)**\n\n#### Core Functions:\n\n| Function | Lines | Summary |\n|----------|-------|---------|\n| **`buildCandidates`** | 537-685 | Generates candidate titles from lines. Handles hyphen-broken lines, ALL_CAPS coalescing, continuation merging, and generates single/2-line/3-line join candidates with dedup via `seen` Set. |\n| **`normalizeOcrTitle`** | 818-872 | Post-processes extracted titles with 3 steps: (1) dictionary-guided repair via `repairOcrText()`, (2) strip section markers with regex, (3) blind digit→letter substitution for ALL_CAPS text only, (4) title-case conversion only if substitution occurred. |\n| **`repairOcrText`** | 798-810 | Applies word-level dictionary-guided OCR repair by splitting text, isolating alphanumeric cores, and calling `repairOcrWord()` on each. |\n| **`repairOcrWord`** | 744-772 | Attempts dictionary lookup of OCR-corrupted words by generating substitution candidates using `OCR_SUBSTITUTIONS` map and checking against `FOOD_DICTIONARY`. Preserves original casing. |\n| **`findBurstEnd`** | 430-506 | Identifies preamble end by: (1) skipping \"PREVIOUS RECIPE OVERFLOW\" blocks, (2) skipping garbled short lines, (3) skipping 5+ consecutive cooking instructions, (4) skipping 3+ consecutive prose lines (lowercase start/continuation). Returns first valid candidate position. **Key threshold: 5 consecutive instructions (line 484).** |\n| **`passesCorroboration`** | 243-268 | Validates candidates via vocabulary corroboration: short candidates (≤3 content words) require 100% match in other lines; longer candidates require ≥67%. Used to filter orphaned multi-title artifacts. |\n| **`isSectionLabel`** | 190-197 | Detects section labels via `SECTION_LABELS` set (case/diacritic-insensitive). Handles OCR variant where leading \"l\" corrupts \"I\" (e.g., \"lngredients\"). |\n| **`looksLikeMetadata`** | 226-228 | Tests text against `METADATA_PATTERNS` regex set (serves/makes/yields, times, yields). |\n\n#### Constants & Patterns:\n\n| Item | Lines | Content |\n|------|-------|---------|\n| **`OCR_ARTIFACT_PATTERN`** | 738 | `/[0-9¡Íí€]/` — matches any digit or OCR corruption characters that might indicate OCR issues. |\n| **`OCR_SUBSTITUTIONS`** | 728-736 | Dictionary mapping OCR artifacts to possible letters: `\"0\": [\"o\"], \"1\": [\"i\", \"l\"], \"4\": [\"a\"], \"5\": [\"s\"], \"¡\": [\"i\"], \"í\": [\"i\", \"l\"], \"€\": [\"e\"]` |\n| **`SECTION_LABELS`** | 115-167 | 70+ labels including English (ingredients, directions, serving, etc.) and Polish equivalents (składniki, przygotowanie, etc.). Includes both process labels and food categories. |\n| **`CATEGORY_SECTION_LABELS`** | 173-183 | Subset of `SECTION_LABELS` for food-group/chapter labels only (e.g., \"vegetables\", \"soups\", \"warzywa\", \"zupy\"). Can legitimately end compound titles. |\n| **`maxPositionalBoost`** | 1048 | **Hard cap of 0.15** on combined positional bonuses (candidate-relative position + first-after-preamble). Prevents over-boosting when both bonuses fire together. |\n\n#### Dedup Filter (Substring Check):\n\n**Location:** Lines 1376-1386 (main dedup logic)\n\n```\nselected = selected.filter((a) => {\n  const aLower = a.text.toLowerCase();\n  // Protect compound titles — these use explicit separators\n  if (/ [+:&] /.test(a.text)) return true;\n  return !selected.some(\n    (b) =>\n      b !== a &&\n      aLower.includes(b.text.toLowerCase()) &&\n      b.text.length < a.text.length\n  );\n});\n```\n\n**Logic:** If candidate `a` is a substring of another candidate `b` and `b` is shorter, remove `a`. Exception: protect compound titles with separators (` + `, ` : `, ` & `). **Shorter always wins** (e.g., \"Pierogi Ruskie\" beats \"Pierogi Ruskie 200g mąki\").\n\nPre-filters (lines 1314-1368) also handle:\n- Sub-section headers followed by ingredients (ALL_CAPS lines)\n- Prefix singles whose continuation join survived\n- Position-0 compound titles protection from distant headers\n\n#### Multi-Title Guard:\n\n**Location:** Lines 1388-1470 (major control flow)\n\n**Three cases:**\n\n1. **≥2 ALL_CAPS survivors** (lines 1397-1426): Keep all, or filter via vocabulary corroboration. Detect if they're section headers (immediately followed by ingredients) vs. actual multi-title page.\n2. **Exactly 1 ALL_CAPS survivor** (lines 1427-1447): If in last 25% of document → likely category footer. Prefer earlier candidates if available.\n3. **Zero ALL_CAPS survivors** (lines 1449-1469): If spread >10 lines apart → body-text leakage, collapse to highest-scoring. If ≤10 lines → likely genuine multi-recipe content, keep all.\n\n#### First-After-Preamble Bonus Logic:\n\n**Location:** Lines 1023-1055\n\n- **Applied to first candidate only** (line 1024)\n- **Bonus amount:** `const preambleBonus = 0.10;` (line 1027)\n- **Capping logic** (lines 1046-1055): Total positional boost (relative position + preamble) capped at `maxPositionalBoost = 0.15`\n\n---\n\n### **File 2: `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/food-dictionary.ts` (146 lines)**\n\n| Item | Lines | Summary |\n|------|-------|---------|\n| **`FOOD_DICTIONARY`** | 7-146 | `Set<string>` of 400+ words: English/Polish ingredients, cooking verbs, dish types, descriptors, and structural recipe title words. Used by `repairOcrWord()` for dictionary-guided OCR repair. All lowercase, diacritic-free for OCR resilience. |\n| **`CATEGORY_SECTION_LABELS`** | — | Referenced in title-extractor, not defined here. (Defined in title-extractor.ts lines 173-183) |\n\n---\n\n## Key Insights\n\n1. **Blind digit→letter substitution** (lines 832-863 of normalizeOcrTitle): Only applied to ALL_CAPS text. Mixed-case text uses per-word logic (digits between lowercase letters → lowercase letters). This prevents over-correction of mixed-case titles.\n\n2. **Dedup substring filter** preserves **shorter candidates** — the opposite of greedy suffix removal. Works correctly because pre-filters remove structural headers that would otherwise block longer forms.\n\n3. **Cooking instruction prologue threshold**: 5+ consecutive cooking instructions (line 484 of findBurstEnd) signal a preamble to skip.\n\n4. **Multi-title guard** is a sophisticated state machine balancing three detection modes (ALL_CAPS density, spread distance, ingredient proximity) to avoid false multi-title collapses.\n\n5. **Corroboration filter** (lines 1402-1404) is applied only when ≥2 ALL_CAPS candidates exist, catching orphaned artifacts from preceding pages.\n\nAll file paths are absolute and ready for reference in your improvement plan implementation."}],"totalDurationMs":89340,"totalTokens":110306,"totalToolUseCount":22,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":249,"cache_read_input_tokens":108032,"output_tokens":2024,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":249},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
